</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[506,572,261,287]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[506,572,261,287]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Mendonca, Rafael &amp; Ale-Rocha, 2007" authorityName="Mendonca, Rafael &amp; Ale-Rocha" authorityYear="2007" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Porphyrochroa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hipandriociliaris">
<emphasis box="[815,1043,261,286]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">P. hipandriociliaris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mendonca" pageId="8" pageNumber="39" refString="Mendonca, M. N., Rafael, J. A. &amp; Ale-Rocha, R. (2007) Descricao de tres especies novas de Porphyrochroa Melander (Diptera, Empididae) da Bacia Amazonica, Brasil. Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 51 (3), 352 - 357." type="journal article" year="2007">
Mendonça, Rafael &amp; Ale-Rocha, 
<number box="[151,210,301,327]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
due to the presence of posterior hypandrial projection and due to the basal cercal lobe posteriorly projected. It differs due to the form of the hypandrium, obeliskform and with normal apex.
</paragraph>
